WEBVTT

00:01.377 --> 00:04.338
When you work here,
you don't think about home

00:04.339 --> 00:06.173
and families and babies.
- That's not fair.

00:06.174 --> 00:07.716
He couldn't have known he was
gonna have a baby a year--

00:07.717 --> 00:09.217
Let me tell you something,
Stephanie.

00:09.218 --> 00:11.136
Maybe you don't know
how babies are made,

00:11.137 --> 00:12.930
because when people are trying,
they know they're trying!

00:12.931 --> 00:15.182
And just because no one ever
wants to try with you

00:15.183 --> 00:16.642
doesn't give you the right

00:16.643 --> 00:18.602
to tell me
how to run my associates!

00:18.603 --> 00:21.647
I got an offer for more money
than I'll see my whole life,

00:21.648 --> 00:24.274
and you want me to turn it down
based on a feeling

00:24.275 --> 00:26.067
that whatever happened to Chris
happened to other people?

00:26.068 --> 00:27.611
You're dating
your therapist.

00:27.612 --> 00:29.321
I don't need a lecture
from you, Louis.

00:29.322 --> 00:30.865
Does Donna have any idea
about the two of you?

00:30.866 --> 00:32.448
No, she doesn't,

00:32.450 --> 00:35.243
and for right now,
I'd like to keep it that way.

00:35.244 --> 00:36.954
Harvey, is there something
that you're not telling me?

00:36.955 --> 00:38.580
‘Cause it seems like you've been
different lately.

00:38.581 --> 00:40.916
We win this, you're gonna be
Andy Dufresne

00:40.917 --> 00:42.417
sitting on a beach in Mexico

00:42.418 --> 00:44.169
with a bank account
full of cash.

00:44.170 --> 00:45.713
I already make
a nice living in here.

00:45.714 --> 00:47.506
I was thinking
maybe some of that money

00:47.507 --> 00:49.174
might go to your
daughter.

00:49.175 --> 00:50.592
I wasn't lying about working
a case with Oliver.

00:50.593 --> 00:51.969
I just didn't tell you
which one.

00:51.970 --> 00:53.971
- The prison one?
- Yeah.

00:53.972 --> 00:56.765
- This is a fireable offense.
- Harvey isn't gonna fire me.

00:56.766 --> 00:59.226
Yeah, but maybe he should.
What is your word worth?

00:59.227 --> 01:02.187
The way things are going, it's
not gonna be worth very much.

01:10.238 --> 01:11.989
Hey.

01:11.990 --> 01:14.033
Hey.

01:14.034 --> 01:16.493
How long have you been up?

01:16.494 --> 01:19.538
A while.

01:19.539 --> 01:22.207
I've been thinking about what
you said to me last night.

01:22.208 --> 01:26.045
Mike, I didn't mean
to be so harsh.

01:26.046 --> 01:28.005
No, you were right.

01:28.006 --> 01:32.091
My word does mean
everything to me...

01:32.092 --> 01:34.887
which is why I'm gonna keep
helping Oliver.

01:34.888 --> 01:36.430
What?

01:36.431 --> 01:38.891
When I gave my word
to Harvey, I meant it.

01:38.892 --> 01:41.100
But before that, I gave
my word to Oscar Reyes.

01:41.101 --> 01:43.437
And I'm sorry,
but I-I can't back out now.

01:43.438 --> 01:45.647
Okay.

01:45.648 --> 01:48.233
So you're just gonna live
your life keeping secrets again?

01:48.234 --> 01:51.028
- This isn't like that.
- How is it not like that?

01:51.029 --> 01:52.863
You're keeping this
from Harvey.

01:52.864 --> 01:54.281
And Harvey kept things
from Jessica.

01:54.282 --> 01:56.157
Look at how that turned out.

01:56.158 --> 01:58.744
I tell Harvey now, and it's
the same as if he catches me.

01:58.745 --> 02:00.746
The case gets tossed,
and all of the people

02:00.747 --> 02:02.998
we're trying to help
keep getting abused.

02:02.999 --> 02:05.960
It's the same as before.

02:05.961 --> 02:08.461
No, Rachel, this is not
the same as when I was a fraud.

02:08.463 --> 02:09.964
And I'll tell you
something else--

02:09.965 --> 02:11.840
I used to have trouble
sleeping at night,

02:11.841 --> 02:13.216
but I sleep like a baby now

02:13.217 --> 02:15.761
because I am helping
these people.

02:15.762 --> 02:19.474
I'm sorry, but that's
the word that I'm keeping.

02:25.396 --> 02:27.064
Good morning.

02:27.065 --> 02:28.899
Hey.
Did you sleep well?

02:28.900 --> 02:31.192
If you consider eight hours
of bliss sleeping well,

02:31.193 --> 02:35.781
then, yes,
I slept very well.

02:35.782 --> 02:37.741
But now I have to go.

02:37.742 --> 02:39.827
- Wait.
- Harvey, I have patients.

02:39.828 --> 02:42.412
I know, but I wanted to get
your opinion on something.

02:42.413 --> 02:45.874
What have you done
this time?

02:45.875 --> 02:49.795
I haven't told Donna
we're seeing each other yet.

02:49.796 --> 02:51.254
Why not?

02:51.255 --> 02:52.923
Come on, you know
my history with her.

02:52.924 --> 02:55.174
We're working together.
I just promoted her.

02:55.175 --> 02:57.176
That's more an excuse
than a reason, isn't it?

02:57.177 --> 02:58.720
I don't want to create
a problem when there isn't one.

02:58.721 --> 03:00.221
And who says
there has to be one?

03:00.222 --> 03:02.099
There doesn't
have to be one, but--

03:02.100 --> 03:05.352
Harvey, first of all, you may
be underestimating her.

03:05.353 --> 03:07.228
I mean, Donna's a big girl.
- Paula--

03:07.229 --> 03:08.856
And second of all,
if I'm wrong

03:08.857 --> 03:10.858
and you're not
underestimating her,

03:10.859 --> 03:12.693
then you're only gonna
cause both of you

03:12.694 --> 03:14.695
a lot more trouble down
the road when she finds out.

03:14.696 --> 03:17.156
‘Cause, Harvey,
she is gonna find out.

03:17.157 --> 03:20.241
So you're telling me
to tell her?

03:20.242 --> 03:22.619
You already know
what you need to do.

03:22.620 --> 03:24.454
You just asked me
because sometimes we need

03:24.455 --> 03:27.041
to hear it
from someone else.

03:35.884 --> 03:37.592
They didn't tell me
you brought a sidekick.

03:37.593 --> 03:39.053
Frank, this is Oliver Grady.

03:39.054 --> 03:40.387
He's the one
that's trying the case.

03:40.388 --> 03:41.930
Good for him.

03:41.931 --> 03:43.348
I still don't know
what you're doing back here.

03:43.349 --> 03:45.350
I already told you
everything I know.

03:45.351 --> 03:47.186
Not everything. It's time you
gave us the name of your source.

03:47.187 --> 03:48.896
Uh-uh.

03:48.897 --> 03:50.814
The deal is that money
goes into my daughter's account,

03:50.815 --> 03:52.399
then you get the name.

03:52.400 --> 03:54.651
What the hell is this?
- It's a down payment.

03:54.652 --> 03:56.361
Down payment?
I don't think so.

03:56.362 --> 03:58.113
I want the whole thing.
- And if you think

03:58.114 --> 03:59.656
we're giving you half a million
without a name,

03:59.657 --> 04:01.200
then you're out of your mind.

04:01.201 --> 04:02.993
Then we are at what
they call an impasse,

04:02.994 --> 04:05.079
because I'm not giving you
that name without that money.

04:05.080 --> 04:06.663
And there isn't
gonna be any money

04:06.664 --> 04:08.415
if the judge
dismisses this case.

04:08.416 --> 04:10.167
What the hell
is he talking about?

04:10.168 --> 04:11.710
He's talking about the fact
that the other side

04:11.711 --> 04:13.378
filed a motion
to dismiss this thing.

04:13.379 --> 04:14.922
Goes to court tomorrow.

04:14.923 --> 04:16.255
If you don't give me
the name of your source,

04:16.257 --> 04:17.591
it's gonna get tossed.

04:17.591 --> 04:19.134
Bullshit
it's gonna get tossed.

04:19.135 --> 04:20.594
I already admitted to you
I took part in it.

04:20.595 --> 04:22.053
It's not enough.

04:22.055 --> 04:23.805
Why is that not enough?
You got my word.

04:23.806 --> 04:25.473
We got no corroboration
of your word.

04:25.474 --> 04:26.892
What's to say you didn't
make up this whole thing

04:26.893 --> 04:28.309
when I came in here?

04:28.310 --> 04:29.853
Then go to
the goddamn prosecutor

04:29.854 --> 04:31.230
I went to seven years ago.

04:31.231 --> 04:32.731
She's got it all on record.

04:32.732 --> 04:34.315
I thought she didn't
pursue this case.

04:34.316 --> 04:36.068
Then you didn't
hear me right.

04:36.069 --> 04:37.861
She pursued it. She just
didn't want to see it through.

04:37.862 --> 04:39.821
Ask her if I'm telling
the truth.

04:39.822 --> 04:42.241
In the meantime,
keep your pocket change,

04:42.242 --> 04:44.743
‘cause you're not getting
shit from me.

04:51.000 --> 04:54.836
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

04:54.837 --> 04:58.257
♪ Get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

04:58.258 --> 05:01.509
♪ Everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

05:01.510 --> 05:05.180
♪ Everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

05:05.181 --> 05:08.058
♪ I'll even eat a bean pie,
I don't mind ♪

05:08.059 --> 05:12.104
♪ Me and Missy is so busy,
busy making money ♪

05:12.105 --> 05:13.772
♪ All right ♪

05:13.773 --> 05:15.068
♪ All step back,
I'm ‘bout to dance ♪

