05:25.161 --> 05:27.287
Hey, buddy.

05:27.288 --> 05:28.830
Louis, I was just
making a cup of coffee.

05:28.831 --> 05:30.790
I'm not taking
any time off, I swear.

05:30.791 --> 05:34.334
Whoa, Brian, it's okay to
take a break every now and then.

05:34.335 --> 05:36.671
- It is?
- Yeah, absolutely.

05:36.672 --> 05:39.299
In fact, coffee preparation
is very important.

05:39.300 --> 05:42.426
Yeah. Actually, making coffee
is one of my favorite hobb--

05:42.427 --> 05:44.012
That's great. Listen to me,
I need to ask you something.

05:44.013 --> 05:46.306
The other day when
I said those things to you

05:46.307 --> 05:47.974
about taking time off,
I mean, I don't even know

05:47.975 --> 05:50.143
if you remember it.
- Like it was yesterday.

05:50.144 --> 05:54.063
Well, in that case
I was just wondering...

05:54.064 --> 05:56.356
how bad was I?

05:56.357 --> 05:58.527
You weren't that bad.

06:01.989 --> 06:04.032
Good.

06:04.033 --> 06:08.328
Now, would you be willing
to swear to that in court?

06:08.329 --> 06:10.370
- What? Why?
- No reason.

06:10.371 --> 06:13.291
Truth is, my recollection is
exactly the same as yours.

06:13.292 --> 06:15.793
You asked for a couple days off,
and I gave it to you.

06:15.794 --> 06:17.461
See, I even wrote it
in my diary.

06:17.462 --> 06:19.255
“Gave Brian two days off.
Felt good about it.”

06:19.256 --> 06:21.216
It looks like you just
wrote that today.

06:21.217 --> 06:23.176
- What makes you say that?
- It has today's date on top.

06:23.177 --> 06:26.470
I just wrote that down to
remember today's conversation.

06:26.471 --> 06:28.181
Can I go back to work now?

06:28.182 --> 06:30.766
Yep, just make sure you have
the affidavit on my desk

06:30.767 --> 06:32.853
as soon as possible.

06:35.064 --> 06:37.815
Thanks for seeing us on such
short notice, Ms. Randolph.

06:37.816 --> 06:39.734
I have to say, when I heard
the name Frank Gallo,

06:39.735 --> 06:41.903
my interest was piqued.
What's this about?

06:41.904 --> 06:43.821
We're representing
a class of prisoners

06:43.822 --> 06:46.282
suing Reform Corporation
for abusive practices.

06:46.283 --> 06:48.450
We're here to confirm that
Frank Gallo came to see you

06:48.451 --> 06:51.037
seven years ago and admitted to
being involved in a conspiracy.

06:51.038 --> 06:53.831
Yeah, he came to me offering
to be an informant

06:53.832 --> 06:56.334
in exchange for protection from
what was going on in Lambert.

06:56.335 --> 06:58.169
And did you believe
what he told you?

06:58.170 --> 07:00.046
Of course I believed him.
He was beaten up,

07:00.047 --> 07:01.463
and he'd been in the infirmary
for two goddamn weeks.

07:01.464 --> 07:02.965
Well, if you believed him,

07:02.966 --> 07:04.675
why the hell didn't you
pursue the case?

07:04.676 --> 07:06.426
I did pursue it.
I ran it up the flagpole,

07:06.427 --> 07:08.512
and it came back down
like a concrete block.

07:08.513 --> 07:10.181
No one gives a shit
about prisoners

07:10.182 --> 07:12.016
or the way they're treated.

07:12.017 --> 07:14.018
So, instead, he offered to
inform on his fellow inmates,

07:14.019 --> 07:16.229
and then he used that to get
himself transferred.

07:16.230 --> 07:18.981
Exactly.
Now, if you don't mind.

07:18.982 --> 07:21.025
Well, Danielle,
in fact, I do mind.

07:21.026 --> 07:23.485
You see, I do give a shit
about how prisoners are treated,

07:23.486 --> 07:26.614
which means you
are gonna tell the court

07:26.615 --> 07:28.574
exactly what you just told us.

07:28.575 --> 07:30.826
Did you not hear
what I just said?

07:30.827 --> 07:33.788
It came back down on me
like a concrete block.

07:33.789 --> 07:35.664
This is my career. I--

07:35.665 --> 07:38.084
I am not gonna go on record
and jeopardize it.

07:38.085 --> 07:40.044
Well, then this is gonna
go one of two ways.

07:40.045 --> 07:42.297
You give us your records,
and we submit them quietly...

07:42.298 --> 07:43.798
Or we subpoena your records

07:43.799 --> 07:45.133
under the Freedom
of Information Act

07:45.134 --> 07:46.842
and put you on the stand.

07:46.843 --> 07:48.552
And seeing as you're afraid
of ruining your career,

07:48.553 --> 07:49.845
I suggest you go
with option A.

07:51.598 --> 07:53.975
You're a couple
of little shits.

07:53.976 --> 07:56.352
Good, you're here.

07:56.353 --> 07:58.229
Listen, there's something
I've been wanting

07:58.230 --> 07:59.563
to talk to you about.

07:59.564 --> 08:00.940
Harvey, it's gonna
have to wait.

08:00.941 --> 08:02.691
Donna, it's important.

08:02.692 --> 08:04.277
Frank Gallo left a message
for you a few minutes ago.

08:04.278 --> 08:06.028
- What did he say?
- He said you and Mike

08:06.029 --> 08:07.905
better not be trying
to screw him over again,

08:07.906 --> 08:09.865
or you're gonna regret it.

08:09.866 --> 08:11.700
Harvey, what's
he talking about?

08:11.701 --> 08:14.287
I don't know, but I'm sure
as hell gonna find out.

08:17.791 --> 08:20.752
What the hell are you
doing with Frank Gallo?

08:22.671 --> 08:24.046
Harvey--

08:24.047 --> 08:25.840
Don't pretend
like you don't know.

08:25.841 --> 08:27.758
He just left me a message
asking me to make sure

08:27.759 --> 08:29.677
that you don't fuck him over.

08:29.678 --> 08:32.054
I told you, I'm working on a
Brooklyn Housing Authority case.

08:32.054 --> 08:34.182
Gallo is from Brooklyn.
He knows people.

08:34.183 --> 08:36.183
And don't tell me he's making
you pay for his information.

08:36.184 --> 08:38.811
Yes, he is,
and I'm gonna pay him.

08:38.812 --> 08:41.522
Mike, odds are
he doesn't know jack shit

08:41.523 --> 08:43.107
and he's just using you
to get money.

08:43.107 --> 08:45.067
No, I looked into it,
all right?

08:45.068 --> 08:46.986
What he told me checks out. He's
on the right side of this thing.

08:46.987 --> 08:49.489
You're telling me he's
all of a sudden Mother Teresa?

08:49.490 --> 08:51.115
This guy tried to kill you!

08:51.116 --> 08:52.950
I know that. Look,
I'm not saying he's a saint.

08:52.951 --> 08:54.535
I'm saying that I know
what I'm doing.

08:54.536 --> 08:56.287
Don't you get it?

08:56.288 --> 08:59.748
A guy like Gallo finds people
to get revenge on.

08:59.749 --> 09:01.667
He thinks about it
and thinks about it,

09:01.668 --> 09:04.086
and the only way
to survive that

09:04.087 --> 09:07.089
is to stay out of his mind
and let him find someone else.

09:07.090 --> 09:09.050
Maybe you're right,
but I already promised him

09:09.051 --> 09:11.552
something for his information,
and if I back out of that now,

09:11.553 --> 09:14.180
I'm gonna end up
on the top of his list.

09:14.181 --> 09:16.724
Does Rachel know
about this?

09:19.353 --> 09:20.895
- No.
- Then you better hope

09:20.896 --> 09:22.438
Gallo doesn't leave
her a message

09:22.439 --> 09:24.399
the same way
he left me one.

09:29.738 --> 09:31.947
Staring
out the window, Louis?

09:31.948 --> 09:33.782
That's a sign that
something's going on.

09:33.783 --> 09:35.410
Nothing's going on, Rachel.

09:35.411 --> 09:37.328
Then why exactly
did you make Brian Altman

09:37.329 --> 09:39.372
relive that horrible day?

09:39.373 --> 09:41.332
- Which horrible day?
- The one where you

09:41.333 --> 09:43.167
treated him like shit because
you were losing your mind.

09:43.168 --> 09:44.502
That day.

09:44.503 --> 09:46.087
You want to know
what's going on?

09:46.088 --> 09:48.714
I'm being sued.
That's what's going on.

09:48.715 --> 09:50.883
- By Brian?
- No, by Stephanie.

09:50.884 --> 09:53.511
For sexual harassment?
Louis, this is bad.

09:53.512 --> 09:55.596
- I know what it is, Rachel.
- Well, then we need to talk

09:55.597 --> 09:57.432
about how
you're gonna handle it.

09:57.433 --> 09:58.807
No, we need to talk about
how you're gonna handle it.

09:58.808 --> 10:00.017
Louis, that's not
a good idea.

10:00.018 --> 10:01.894
It's the only good idea.

10:01.895 --> 10:03.687
You need to go over there right
now and put an end to this.

10:03.688 --> 10:05.440
- I can't do that.
- Why not?

10:05.441 --> 10:07.483
Because I had a run-in
with Stephanie after you did,

10:07.484 --> 10:09.360
and then I had another run-in
with her after Donna fired her.

10:09.361 --> 10:11.153
She's not gonna listen to me.

10:11.154 --> 10:12.572
It is sexual harassment,
Rachel.

10:12.573 --> 10:14.240
I cannot have it
on my record.

10:14.241 --> 10:16.075
Someone needs to convince her
to let this go,

10:16.076 --> 10:17.910
and it needs to be
a lawyer I can trust,

10:17.911 --> 10:20.079
but it also needs to be someone
who's close to her level,

10:20.080 --> 10:21.914
or she's gonna feel attacked.

10:21.915 --> 10:25.127
Then I think I have
the perfect choice.

10:30.048 --> 10:32.508
Katrina.

10:32.509 --> 10:34.594
I take it Louis
got my lawsuit.

10:34.595 --> 10:38.013
He did, and I'm here to ask
why you're bringing it now.

10:38.014 --> 10:40.308
Because the things
you're alleging he said--

10:40.309 --> 10:42.726
Alleging he said?

10:42.727 --> 10:46.855
Wow. I guess it's lawyer first,
friend second.

10:46.856 --> 10:49.024
That's not fair. I'm only
here because we're friends.

10:49.025 --> 10:50.943
And because you wanted
to convince me to forget

10:50.944 --> 10:53.070
that Pearson Specter Litt
ruined my career.

10:53.071 --> 10:55.781
Stephanie,
I know you got fired,

10:55.782 --> 10:59.619
but this lawsuit
could destroy Louis.

10:59.620 --> 11:01.287
Let me get this straight.

11:01.288 --> 11:03.372
The woman who convinced me
to leave a good job

11:03.373 --> 11:05.249
for one where I was
treated terribly,

11:05.250 --> 11:07.168
sexually harassed,
and then fired

11:07.169 --> 11:09.795
is now asking me
for a personal favor?

11:09.796 --> 11:12.465
Yes, I am.

11:16.052 --> 11:18.846
Well, I'm not in the mood
to grant one.

11:18.847 --> 11:23.434
So you can tell Louis
I will see him in court.

11:23.435 --> 11:25.186
Stephanie, the woman I knew

11:25.187 --> 11:27.313
at Rand Kaldor Zane
wouldn't do this.

11:27.314 --> 11:30.024
Please...

11:30.025 --> 11:32.109
tell me what's going on
so I can help.

11:35.322 --> 11:37.239
I heard people here talking,

11:37.240 --> 11:40.868
and they said that I got fired
because I couldn't hack it.

11:40.869 --> 11:43.663
Well, that's not true,

11:43.664 --> 11:46.207
and I won't have them
thinking it is.

11:46.208 --> 11:47.916
Then close that door
and sit down,

11:47.917 --> 11:49.627
because I'm betting that
we can work out a deal

11:49.628 --> 11:52.338
right now
that shows anyone

11:52.339 --> 11:55.634
who's ever underestimated you
just how strong you are.

11:58.679 --> 12:00.638
Alex, have you seen Donna
by any chance?

12:00.639 --> 12:03.140
- What?
- Donna. Have you seen her?

12:03.141 --> 12:05.059
I need to tell her something.
- I don't know, Harvey.

12:05.060 --> 12:06.852
I don't have time to track
your former secretary's

12:06.853 --> 12:08.229
every damn move.

12:08.230 --> 12:09.855
What the hell's
wrong with you?

12:09.856 --> 12:11.691
I'll tell you
what's wrong with me.

12:11.692 --> 12:13.442
Masterson Construction's
pissed about this prison case.

12:13.443 --> 12:15.861
Still? You handed it off
like they asked.

12:15.862 --> 12:17.613
No, they wanted the thing
gone, not handed off,

12:17.614 --> 12:19.198
and now it's turned
into a class action,

12:19.199 --> 12:21.200
and it's going
to trial tomorrow.

12:21.201 --> 12:23.869
Listen to me, it's not your
job to make this thing go away.

12:23.870 --> 12:25.580
Harvey, I'm their attorney.
They had a problem,

12:25.581 --> 12:27.289
they wanted it fixed,
and I didn't fix it.

12:27.290 --> 12:29.083
Bullshit, you got
Pearson Specter to drop it

12:29.084 --> 12:31.126
like a hot potato.
That's all you could've done.

12:31.127 --> 12:33.170
No, what I could have done
was kill the whole damn thing.

12:33.171 --> 12:35.631
And since I didn't, they found
some inmate at another prison

12:35.632 --> 12:37.174
to break the case wide open,

12:37.175 --> 12:39.843
which is why I just had
to eat a ton of shit.

12:39.844 --> 12:42.346
- What did you just say?
- I said they found a witness

12:42.347 --> 12:46.267
at another prison, and now I'm
gonna lost my goddamn client.

12:46.268 --> 12:47.685
Where you going?

12:47.686 --> 12:50.229
Like I said,
I need to find Donna.

12:54.109 --> 12:59.238
I want to know right now,
do you know where Mike is?

12:59.239 --> 13:01.907
- No, I don't.
- You don't know where,

13:01.908 --> 13:03.825
or you don't know
what case he's working on?

13:03.826 --> 13:05.453
I don't know either one,
but if you calm down,

13:05.454 --> 13:07.121
then maybe I can help you
find him.

13:07.122 --> 13:09.498
No, Rachel, I don't want
help finding him

13:09.499 --> 13:11.500
In fact, I don't want you
telling him

13:11.501 --> 13:13.669
I was looking for him at all.

